Seales (Spanish: Signs) is the first studio album by Argentine pop rock group Erreway. The album was released through Sony Music and Cris Morena Group on 29 July 2002 (see 2002 in music). It was produced by Cris Morena and Carlos Nilson, who wrote all songs for the album. Seales sold over 1 million copies worldwide and topped the Argentine Billboard Albums Chart. It was certified Double Platinum by CAPIF.[1] The song "Rebelde Way" was used as the opening theme for the Cris Morena Group TV soap opera, Rebelde Way (200203), which starred Erreway members Camila Bordonaba, Felipe Colombo, Luisana Lopilato and Benjamn Rojas. The album singles  "Sweet Baby", "Bonita de Ms", "Resistir", "Inmortal", "Amor de Engao" and "Ser Porque Te Quiero"  all enjoyed success in the charts in Argentina, Latin America, Israel and Europe.
